Refresher training is provided at least every three years to each empolyee involved in operating a process to assure that the employy understands and adheres to the curren SOPs of the process.  PPC, in consulation with the employees involved in operating the process, determines the appropriate frequency of refresher training.

PPC ascertains that each employee involved in operating a process has received and understands the required training.  PPC maintains records that contain the identity of the employee, the date of training, and the means used to verify that the employee understood the training.

Mechanical Integrity

PPC has written procedures to maintain the on-going integrity of process equipment, including:

Pressure vessels and storage tanks;
Piping systems (including piping components such as valves);
Relief and Vent System and devices;
Emergency Shutdown Systems;
Controls including monitoring devices and sensors, alarms, and interlocks; and,
Pumps and Compressors.

PPC trains each employee invloved in maintaining the on-going integrity of process equipment in an overview of that process and its hazards.  To assure that the employee can oerform the job tasks in a safe manner, PPC further trains employees in the procedures applicable to the employee's job tasks.  Inspections and tests are preformed on process equipment.  Inspection and testing procedures follow recognized and generally accepted good engineering practices.  The frequency of inspections and tests of process equipment is consistent with applicable manufacturer's recommendations and good engineering practices.  Inspections and tests are conducted more frequently if determined to be necessary by prior operating experience.  PPC documen

